DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros("PG.pl", "PGbasicmacros.pl", "PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

# output the text of the problem

$p = random(100,150,10);
$c = random(100,200,10);
$n = random(200,300,10);
$co1 = $p+$c;
$co2 = $p*$n-2000;


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

The same company produces skies, too. Fixed costs are ${DOLLAR}2000, and
the cost of producing each pair of skies is $DOLLAR$c. The selling price is 
$DOLLAR$co1 (per pair). How many pairs should be sold to make a profit of
$DOLLAR$co2?

$BR

Answer:   \{ans_rule(30)\}

EOT

$ans1 = $n;
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));

